content_sections.content:
Example
Check whether a variable is a number or a numeric string, or not:
<?php
$a = 32;
echo "a is " . is_numeric($a) . "<br>";
$b = 0;
echo "b 
  is " . is_numeric($b) . "<br>";
$c = 32.5;
echo "c is " . is_numeric($c) 
  . "<br>";
$d = "32";
echo "d is " . is_numeric($d) . "<br>";
$e = true;
echo "e is " . is_numeric($e) . "<br>";
$f = null;
echo "f is " . is_numeric($f) . "<br>";
?>

Definition and Usage
The is_numeric() function checks whether a variable is a number or a numeric 
string.
This function returns true (1) if the variable is a number or a numeric 
string, otherwise it returns false/nothing.
Syntax
is_numeric(
variable
);
Parameter Values
Parameter
Description
variable
Required. Specifies the variable to check
Technical Details
Return Value:
TRUE if
variable
is a number or a numeric string, FALSE otherwise
Return Type:
Boolean
PHP Version:
4.0+

★
+1
